Here's the approach:

### 1. Define three `ResourceDictionary` files

Create one per theme (e.g., `Themes/LightTheme.xaml`, `DarkTheme.xaml`, `HighContrastTheme.xaml`):

```xml
<!-- Themes/LightTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="PrimaryText">#1A1A1A</Color>
    <Color x:Key="Accent">#0078D4</Color>
</ResourceDictionary>
```

Use the same keys in every theme file so your UI binds uniformly with `{DynamicResource}`.

### 2. Use `DynamicResource` everywhere

```xml
<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource PageBackground}">
    <Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryText}" Text="Hello" />
</ContentPage>
```

`DynamicResource` (not `StaticResource`) is required so values update at runtime.

### 3. Create a theme-switching helper

```csharp
public enum AppTheme { Light, Dark, HighContrast }

public static class ThemeManager
{
    public static void ApplyTheme(AppTheme theme)
    {
        var mergedDicts = Application.Current!.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
        mergedDicts.Clear();

        mergedDicts.Add(theme switch
        {
            AppTheme.Dark         => new DarkTheme(),
            AppTheme.HighContrast => new HighContrastTheme(),
            _                     => new LightTheme()
        });

        // Persist the choice
        Preferences.Set("app_theme", theme.ToString());
    }

    public static void LoadSavedTheme()
    {
        var saved = Preferences.Get("app_theme", nameof(AppTheme.Light));
        if (Enum.TryParse<AppTheme>(saved, out var theme))
            ApplyTheme(theme);
    }
}
```

### 4. Call on startup

In `App.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    ThemeManager.LoadSavedTheme();
}
```

### 5. Settings page picker

```xml
<Picker x:Name="ThemePicker" Title="Theme"
        ItemsSource="{Binding Themes}"
        SelectedIndexChanged="OnThemeChanged" />
```

```csharp
void OnThemeChanged(object? sender, EventArgs e)
{
    if (ThemePicker.SelectedItem is AppTheme selected)
        ThemeManager.ApplyTheme(selected);
}
```

**Key points:**
- Use **`DynamicResource`** — static won't update at runtime.
- Clear and re-add to `MergedDictionaries` to swap themes.
- Persist with `Preferences` so the choice survives restarts.
- Keep resource keys identical across all three dictionaries.
